<section version="5.0" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
		>

		<title>Widget Issues Division</title>
		<section>
			<title>Binding Applications rule</title>
			<para>
				All Bugtracker management applications of all your projects can be bind to the widget. 
				For configuring applications to bind, please refer to section <xref linkend="widgetCommonSetting" endterm="widgetCommonSettingXref" />.
			</para>
		</section>
		<section>
			<title>Overview</title>
			<para>This widget show the repartition of issues, grouped by state, in the form of a pie chart.
						You can hide or show issues state by clicking on state name and icon in the legend.
					</para>
					<figure>
						<title>Example of widget Issues Division
						</title>
						<mediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata align="center"
									fileref="07-Widget-IssuesDivision-Overview.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</mediaobject>
					</figure>
					
		</section>
		<section>
			<title>Widget parameters</title>
			<figure>
				<title>Configuration of widget properties</title>
				<mediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata align="center"
							fileref="07-Widget-IssuesDivision-Setting.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</mediaobject>
			</figure>
			<para>
				This menu allow you to :
				<itemizedlist>
					<listitem>
						<para>Modify widget title in your dashboard, by editing "name" field
						</para>
					</listitem>
					<listitem>
						<para>Select if you want to agregate all issues version, or only a specific one.
						</para>
					</listitem>
					<listitem>
						<para>Save your modifications</para>
					</listitem>
					<listitem>
						<para>Return to dashboard, by clicking on the return button at top right.
						</para>
					</listitem>
				</itemizedlist>
			</para>
		</section>
</section>
